commentary: Patel to Amla, OUT they're going to have to reconsider the ramp! Amla walks across once more, but this time he's pushed it flat and back of a length. Amla is still moving as it arrives at him with all stumps exposed. In the end, he can't get down fast, or stay still to play with a straight bat. Gets hurried on the ramp, takes it on the inside edge outside off and it clips off stump...in fact, it's hit middle, but only the bail on the left has lit up

commentary: Morris to Guptill, 2 runs lofts one straight down the ground and what an effort from AB de Villiers at mid-off. Flings himself full length to his right and had he snaffled that, it would have been one of the best catches in recent memory. Guptill lofted it straight down the ground and de Villiers just came running out of nowhere but could not get to it. De Villiers had to first run quite some distance to his right, which he does and puts in a full-length dive and gets his hands to it but cannot hold on to it. 150 for Guptill and he gets a standing ovation
